              Just bottled my first specialty grains batch.  Ended at 1.014, which is higher than I wanted, but pretty much inline with what the calculator said would happen with the Munton's dry yeast.  The sample I tried did taste a bit sweet, but not really bad.  I don't think I would like to drink it as it stands now, but we'll see how it tastes after carbonating and aging for a month.  Might have to chalk this up as a learning experience.  Glad I did a half batch in case it turns out bad.<br /><br />I'll do the second half of the batch next weekend, but in the mean time I've acquired some SAF-05, so it will be interesting to see how much of a difference the yeast makes.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
