              Bottle my first two batches over the last week.  Missed the FG on the American Pale Ale by at least 5 points (target .012-.015 and I was .02) and think the room may have been a bit too chilly (66-70F).  I failed to take an OG on the English Brown in the second back but hit the kit's target FG.  Neither tasted particularly good but I know there is a lot to come during carbonation so I'm not going to start worrying yet.<br /><br />I've got an IPA that I need to transfer and add dry hops to. It's been in fermenter for 2 weeks and I'll the hops and give it one more in secondary.  Two more kits to go before I start with the grain I brought over.<br /><br />For water, I get mine from the spigot and run it through a culligan filter.

              

              
              
