          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              The room I was keeping my bottles in for carbing was getting into the low to mid 70s during the day, so I moved them to the basement.  For the last few days the basement has been a very consistent 63-64 degrees day or night.  The Munton's yeast says it prefers 65-70 degrees, so this might result in a little bit of under carbonation.  My next batch will use SAF-05 which is supposed to tolerate down to 59 degrees, so the basement won't be as much of a problem with that.  I guess if it comes down to it I would prefer slightly flat beer to vinegar.

              

              
              
