        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              At the point of Bottle carbing, +/- 5F isn't a big deal. Fermentation temps refer to primary, and are an indicator of the ideal fermentation flavor profile. So for example, a Hefe yeast does the vast majority of fermentation at 67, it might tend to be clovey, but at 73 it might trend towards banana esthers. <br /><br />The relatively tiny amount of fermentation occurring during carbing isn't typically considered to be a big contributor to flavor.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
