              OK.  I kept the bucket at a pretty consistent 66-68 during primary, so it should be happy with that.<br /><br />I think fermentation temp is probably what ruined my last Mr. Beer batch.  I wasn't really bothering to track the temperature, but it spent all of its time in a room that was in the low 70s pretty much all day.  Not sure what kind of yeast comes with the Mr. Beer kits, but it probably doesn't like temps over 70.

              

              
              
