          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Second half-batch is in primary now.  I misestimated how much the empty LME bottle would weigh, and it seems that when I tried to split the LME in half I shorted my previous batch by 5-6 oz (which ended up in this batch instead).  That probably explains why my OG was slightly low last time, and a little high this time.  It was supposed to be 1.043, came in at 1.041 last time and 1.048 this time.  I wish there was an option of ordering the kit with 2 3lb bottles instead of 1 6lb bottle.  That's the only part of splitting these kits in half that's giving me trouble.  However, with an accurate weight for the empty bottle now I should be able to get closer next time.<br /><br />I've switched a few things up.  I'm using SAF-05 yeast instead of the Muntun's dry.  On a recommendation from a friend, I'm also using Buhl water instead of the Target brand spring water.  The price difference was negligible.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
