          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              I think as long as you haven't picked up any wild yeast or an infection in the mean time, then you just repitch.  However, sometimes it can take a day or so to get going.  I pitched around 4pm yesterday, didn't see any bubbling by 10pm, but was getting regular bubbling by the time I woke up this morning.  That was with SAF-05 which is supposed to be a pretty rapid yeast (but I also didn't bother using a starter, I just pitched it in dry after aeration).

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
