              Brewed this one today, was tired of having nothing in the fermenter.  Left the house to pick it up @ 11 and had it in the carboy and yeast pitched by 3:30<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.greatfermentations.com/Honey-Wheat-Kit/productinfo/BKA021/">http://www.greatfermentations.com/Honey ... fo/BKA021/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />I replaced my 10# regulator on my jet burner w/ a 20# one.  Wow. At 1/2 blast got a full 5 gallons to a boil in about 20 mins.<br /><br />I also stopped by the local beer merchant and got a bomber of Upland Ard Ri to go with dinner.  I've heard good things and can't wait to try it.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
