        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Tettnang is a very mild bittering hop. I'm not familiar with vanguard, but any 5min addition will have very little bittering effect. Take note that honey malt is not actual honey. It's an extremely aromatic malt, smelling somewhat similar to honey. <br /><br />I like not much more than 4 oz of honey in a beer as light as what you describe. I dont have much experience going nearly 50/50 honey vs malt.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
