        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              I had no response on the initial yeast (as expected) so pitched a second batch that immediately got a response.  I bottled my dry hopped IPA as well, with about half of it in a Party Pig. I just dumped the pellets in the carboy and they started to plug up the bottling spigot. I ended up tossing probably 6 beers worth of stuff. It wasn't goign to be worth it as there was plenty of hops suspended in it. Will have to use bags next time.<br /><br /><br />2 more kits until I start whole grain.  <br /><br />My American Pale Ale tastes...if not bad, amateurish.  It was the best smelling of the bunch as wort but it has a sharpness to it that, while drinkable, isn't particularly enjoyable. We'll see how it ages.  The English Brown is a lot better. The dry hopped IPA tasted great out of the fermenter and I'm very excited for it.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
