              It's also possible/probable that whatever process he's using to get great results might not scale up to mass production.<br /><br />---------------------------<br /><br />Bottled my second half-batch today.  FG was 1.011 (calculator estimated 1.012).  The US-05 yeast did a pretty good job since the SG was higher than my last half-batch, but finished lower than that batch.  Didn't taste great at bottling time, but we'll see what a month of aging will do.  One more week until I crack open my first batch to see how that one turned out.

              

              
              
