        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <span style="font-style: italic">Finally</span> cracked open my first bottle.  Poured with about an inch of good looking head.  The head disapated after a minute or two, but left a little lacing on the glass.  It ended up pretty hazy, so I think I'll be investing in some Irish Moss for my next batch.<br /><br />The 4 weeks in bottle really changed the flavor quite a bit.  My notes from bottling were that it tasted sweet a month ago.  Now it actually tastes rather hoppy.  Not at IPA levels, but definitely stronger than I was expecting.  Not quite as strong at the end of the glass, so the carbonation is clearly effecting the flavor.<br /><br />All in all, not too shabby for my first batch.  Next two beers are going to be a Honey Ale (for summer) and eventually a Nut Brown for the winter.

              

              
